cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.GT 

The paper discusses the development and evaluation of general, domain-independent AI technology, specifically in the context of reinforcement learning, model learning, model-based planning, imitation learning, transfer learning, and intrinsic motivation. These topics are all closely related to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses computer vision techniques to process the game environments, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of planning and optimization techniques also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the robotics (cs.RO) or game theory (cs.GT) sub-categories.
